The Johannesburg council has resumed and several former coalition council members have been voted out. The ANC unsurprisingly succeeded in a vote of no confidence against speaker Vasco da Gama after their candidate became the new mayor yesterday.
The EFF abstained, yet votes tallied at 135 in favour of the motion, with 99 against, and thus Da Gama was no longer speaker of the City of Johannesburg.
The ANC has instituted the motion against the speaker as it says that the speaker has failed to safeguard the interests of the council and that he has failed to provide the leadership to ensure the smooth running of the council.
The DA’s chief whip, Kevin Wax, and the DA’s chair of chairs, Alex Christians, may have also been shown the door.
